HEADWORD: Theogony
<hw>The*og"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>theogonia</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ a god + the root of <?/ to be born.
See <er>Theism</er>, and <er>Genus</er>.]</ety> <def>The generation or
genealogy of the gods; that branch of heathen theology which deals with
the origin and descent of the deities; also, a poem treating of such
genealogies; <as>as, the <ex>Theogony</ex> of Hesiod</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

